IRS990.Description: ST FRANCIS HEALTH SERVICES IS A CORPORATION THAT PROVIDES MANAGEMENT, ADMINISTRATION, FINANCE AND DATA PROCESSING SERVICES TO ITS RELATED ORGANIZATIONS IN FURTHERANCE OF THEIR HEALTHCARE MISSIONS. ANOTHER PART OF THE ORGANIZATION IS TO PROVIDE HOME CARE SERVICES IN THE MORRIS AND DULUTH AREAS OF MN. DURING THE CURRENT REPORTING YEAR, MORE THAN 78 CLIENTS WERE SERVED WITH HOME CARE SERVICES. ALSO DURING THIS TIME PERIOD, THE ORGANIZATION EMPLOYED ABOUT 79 FULL TIME EQUIVALENT EMPLOYEES AND GROSS WAGES PAID OUT WERE MORE THAN 3.6 MILLION DOLLARS. THIS WAS ALL PROVIDED IN AN AREA WHERE MEDICAL AND EMPLOYMENT OPPORTUNITIES ARE LIMITED.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: ORGANIZATION'S PROCESS USED TO REVIEW FORM 990
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CFO OF ST. FRANCIS HEALTH SERVICE OF MORRIS, INC REVIEWS THE TAX RETURN.
ANNUALLY THE ORGANIZATION CONDUCTS IN-SERVICE TRAINING REVIEWING THE POLICY ON CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AND REQUIRES THE BOARD MEMBERS, MANAGEMENT STAFF, AND KEY EMPLOYEES TO DISCLOSE CONFLICTS

THE CEO AND OFFICERS ARE EMPLOYEES OF SFHS (A RELATED ORGANIZATION AND UNDER COMMON CONTROL). THE COMPENSATION PROCESS FOR THE CEO - ANNUALLY THE HR DIRECTOR SUBMITS THE CEO'S JOB DESCRIPTION, PERFORMANCE EVALUATION FORM, SFHS' PAY GRADE SCHEDULE AND COMPARABLE WAGE SURVEY(S) TO THE CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD. THE CHAIRMAN AND THE EVALUATION COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD REVIEWS THE PERFORMANCE AND DETERMINES THE SALARY OF THE CEO.

THE CEO AND OFFICERS ARE EMPLOYEES OF SFHS. THE COMPENSATION PROCESS FOR OFFICERS - CEO AND THE HR DIRECTOR REVIEWS COMPARABLE WAGE SURVEY INFORMATION, REVIEWS PERFORMANCE (WITH INPUT FROM THE VP, IF APPROPRIATE) AND DETERMINES SALARY.
THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICTS OF INTEREST POLICIES, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC ON AN AS REQUESTED BASIS.
